# Nutria — canonical design

When editing anything under `Nutria/`, **do not** treat the current five-tab navigator (Home · Planner · Grocery · Log · Settings) as the product source of truth for **layout, locale, or IA**.

## Before UI work

1. Read `Nutria/product/SOURCE_OF_TRUTH.md`.
2. Open `Nutria/product/design-preview.html` in a browser (Hari ini · Rencana · Belanja · Prep).

## Target experience

- **Four primary tabs** (Indonesian labels in target UX): **Hari ini**, **Rencana**, **Belanja**, **Prep** — as modeled in the preview.
- **Legacy app** under `Nutria/app/` is the **migration baseline**, not the design endpoint.

## Specs

Detailed behavior and household-accountability features: initiative docs at `~/Projects/nutria-household-angle/` (`DESIGN.md`, `SPEC.md`, `CHANGE_REQUESTS_SPEC.md`, `SOURCE_OF_TRUTH.md`) if present on disk. If absent, rely on `Nutria/product/` + this rule.

## Conflict resolution

If code and `design-preview.html` disagree on structure or copy **for new work**, align implementation toward the preview and file a follow-up for parity; do not expand legacy patterns without explicit user opt-in.
